The paper deals with the task of Complex Sequential QA, which involves answering factual questions through complex inferencing over a realistic-sized KG of millions of entities and learning to converse through a series of coherently linked QA pairs. This task involves natural language processing, dialog systems, and knowledge graphs, which are all relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the task involves retrieving relevant subgraphs of the KG to answer questions, which is relevant to the sub-categories of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DB (Databases). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL, cs.AI, and cs.LG, followed by cs.IR and cs.DB.
